{"parse":{"title":"oil","pageid":6673,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|OIL|Oil|óil|òil|oïl|-oil}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|en|oyl||obsolete}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|oil|a=UK,US}}, {{IPA|en|/ɔɪl/|[ɔɪʲəɫ]|/ɔj(ɪ)l/<a:Indic,father-bother>|/ɑj(ɪ)l/}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-oil.ogg|a=US}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-oil.ogg|a=UK}}\n** {{homophones|en|Oi'll}}\n** {{rhymes|en|ɔɪl|s=1}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ɔl/|a=Southern US}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-south-oil.ogg|a=Southern US}}\n<!--'all' and 'awl' are not homophones because their vowel is long, while the /ɔ/ here is shortspoken-->\n** {{rhymes|en|ɔl|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|oyle}}, {{m|enm|oile|t=olive oil}}, borrowed from {{der|en|xno|olie}}, from {{der|en|la|oleum|t=oil, olive oil}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἔλαιον|t=olive oil}}, from {{m|grc|ἐλαία|t=olive}}. Compare {{cog|sla-pro|*lojь}}. More at {{m|en|olive}}. {{doublet|en|oleum}}. Supplanted {{cog|enm|ele|t=oil}}, from {{cog|ang|ele|t=oil}}, also from Latin.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q42962}}{{U|liquid}} [[fat]].\n# {{senseid|en|petroleum}} {{U|petroleum}}-based [[liquid]] used as [[fuel]] or [[lubricant]].\n# {{U|petroleum}}.\n#: {{ux|en|'''Oil''' is found in countries such as Saudi Arabia and is transported all over the world.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-08-03|volume=408|issue=8847|magazine=w:The Economist\n|titleurl=http://www.economist.com/news/leaders/21582516-worlds-thirst-oil-could-be-nearing-peak-bad-news-producers-excellent|title=Yesterday’s fuel\n|passage=The dawn of the '''oil''' age was fairly recent. Although the stuff was used to waterproof boats in the Middle East 6,000 years ago, extracting it in earnest began only in 1859 after an '''oil''' strike in Pennsylvania. The first barrels of crude fetched $18 (around $450 at today’s prices). It was used to make kerosene, the main fuel for artificial lighting after overfishing led to a shortage of whale blubber.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802192448/https://www.economist.com/leaders/2013/08/03/yesterdays-fuel}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} An [[oil painting]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1973|author=John Ulric Nef|title=Search for meaning: the autobiography of a nonconformist|page=89|passage=Yet, in another way, I was unable to put Picasso's '''oils''' in the same class as Cezanne's, or even (which will no doubt shock many readers) as Renoir's.}}\n# {{lb|en|painting}} {{U|oil paint}}.\n#: {{ux|en|I prefer to paint in '''oil'''}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|bromoil|butteroil|deoil|enoil|enoiling|lamp oil|nonoil|oilable|oilberg|oilbird|oilcake|oilcloth|oilcoat|oilcrop|oilcup|oildom|oiler|oilfish|oilgae|Oilgate|oiligarch|oilionaire|oilish|oilless|oillike|oilmonger|oilnut|oilocracy|oilometer|oilpaper|oilpatch|oilpresser|oilpressing|oilproof|oilrig|oilseed|oilstone|oilstove|oiltight|oilway|oilworks|petroil|soyoil|wool oil|baby oil||lubricating oil|the squeaky wheel gets the oil\n|burn the midnight oil|Athabasca oil sands|oil of tartar|oil of tartar per deliquium|bronzing oil| hydraulic oil|oil filter|pongamia oil|transmission oil|bean oil|carbon oil\n|castor oil\n|cod liver oil|oil spotting|oil-digger|ore-bulk-oil carrier|rind oil spot|rind-oil spot|Russia oil|take your oil|peanut oil\n|colza oil\n|cooking oil\n|cottonseed oil\n|croton oil\n|crude oil|space oil\n|essential oil\n|evening primrose oil||dino oil|dinosaur oil|kikuel oil\n|fatty oil|oil barrel|oil diaper\n|fixed oil|Oil Islands\n|gas oil\n|gorli oil\n|grapeseed oil\n|green oil\n|illuminating oil\n|infused oil\n|laxative oil\n|linseed oil\n|lubricating oil|fork oil|Koeme oil|mirbane oil|margosa oil|neem oil|oil reservoir|oil terminal|oiticica oil|poppyseed oil|rubbing oil|shaving oil|sperm whale oil|tung oil tree|zdravets oil|oil heater|soyabean oil\n|mineral oil\n|motor oil\n|mustard oil\n|neck oil|phulwara oil|snake oil salesman\n|North Sea oil\n|oil baron\n|oilbath,oil bath|eucalyptus oil|ricinus oil\n|oilbox\n|oil can\n|oilc