f}}, {{tt+|cs|nafta|f}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|olie|c}}, {{tt+|da|råolie|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|olie|f}}, {{tt+|nl|aardolie|f}}, {{tt+|nl|petroleum|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|petrolo}}, {{tt|eo|oleo}}, {{tt|eo|nafto}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|nafta}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|öljy}}, {{tt+|fi|raakaöljy}}, {{tt+|fi|maaöljy}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|pétrole|m}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|petróleo|m}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|ნავთი}}, {{tt|ka|ნავთობი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Erdöl|n}}, {{tt+|de|Öl|n}}, {{tt+|de|Petroleum|n}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|πετρέλαιο|n}}, {{tt+|el|ορυκτέλαιο|m}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|νάφθα|f}}, {{tt|grc|ῥαδινάκη|f}}\n* Gujarati: {{tt|gu|પેટ્રોલિયમ}}\n* Hausa: {{tt|ha|mai}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t-needed|haw}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|שֶׁמֶן|m|tr=shémen}}, {{tt+|he|נֵפְטְ|m|tr=neft}}\n* Hindi: {{tt|hi|पेट्रोलियम|m}}, {{tt+|hi|शिलारस|?}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|olaj}}, {{tt+|hu|kőolaj}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|hráolía|f}}, {{t|is|jarðolía|f}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|minyak bumi}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt|ia|petroleo}}\n* Irish: {{tt+|ga|ola|f}}, {{tt|ga|íle|f}}\n* Istriot: {{tt|ist|pitruolgio|m}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|petrolio|m}}, {{tt+|it|benzina|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|石油|tr=せきゆ, sekiyu}}, {{tt+|ja|油|tr=あぶら, abura}}\n* Jeju: {{t|jje|지름}}\n* Kannada: {{tt|kn|ಪೆಟ್ರೋಲಿಯಮ್}}\n* Kazakh: {{tt+|kk|мұнай}}\n* Khmer: {{tt|km|ប្រេងកាត}}, {{tt+|km|ប្រេង}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|기름}}, {{tt+|ko|석유(石油)}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{tt+|ckb|نەوت}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{tt+|kmr|neft}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{tt+|ky|нефть}}, {{tt+|ky|мунай}}\n* Lao: {{tt+|lo|ນ້ຳມັນ}}, {{tt|lo|ປິໂຖລັຽມ}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|petroleum|n}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|nafta|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt|lt|nafta|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|нафта|f}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|minyak}}, {{tt+|ms|petroleum}}, {{tt|ms|minyak batu}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt+|ml|എണ്ണ}} (fuel), {{tt+|ml|പെട്രോളിയം}}\n* Maltese: {{tt|mt|pitrolju|m}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|तेल|n}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|mn|газрын тос}} {{tt|mn|ᠭᠠᠵᠠᠷ ᠤᠨ ᠲᠣᠰᠤ}}\n*: Mongolian script: {{tt|mn|чулуун тос}} {{tt|mn|ᠴᠢᠯᠠᠭᠤᠨ ᠲᠣᠰᠤ}} {{qualifier|Inner Mongolia}}\n* Mwani: {{tt|wmw|mafuta}}\n* Navajo: {{tt|nv|akʼah}}, {{tt|nv|akʼahkǫʼ}}, {{tt|nv|tókǫʼí}}\n* Nogai: {{tt|nog|напт}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|olje|m|f}}, {{tt+|nb|petroleum|m}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|нафта|f}}\n* Pashto: {{tt+|ps|نفت|m|tr=naft}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{tt|prs|نَفْت}}, {{tt|prs|تیلِ خَاک}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|نَفْت}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{tt|pdt|Steeneelj|f}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|olej|m}}, {{tt+|pl|ropa|f}}, {{tt+|pl|ropa naftowa|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|petróleo|m}}, {{tt+|pt|óleo|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|petrol}}, {{tt+|ro|păcură}}, {{tt+|ro|benzină}}, {{tt+|ro|țiței|n}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|нефть|f}}, {{t+|ru|петро́леум|m}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|ola|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|на̏фта|f}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|nȁfta|f}}\n* Shan: {{tt+|shn|ၼမ်ႉမၼ်း}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt|scn|pitròliu|m}}\n* Sinhalese: {{tt+|si|ඛනිජ තෙල්}}, {{tt|si|ඛණිජ තෙල්}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|ropa|f}}, {{tt|sk|nafta|f}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|nafta|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|petróleo|m}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|olja|c}}, {{tt|sv|bergolja|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|petrolyo}}\n* Tajik: {{tt|tg|нафт}}, {{t+|tg|нефт}}\n* Tamil: {{tt|ta|பெட்ரோலியம்}}\n* Tatar: {{tt|tt|нефть}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|చమురు}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|น้ำมัน}}, {{tt|th|ปิโตรเลียม}}\n* Tigrinya: {{tt|ti|ነዳዲ ዘይቲ}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|petrol}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|nebit}}\n* Udmurt: {{tt|udm|мувӧй}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt|uk|на́фта|f}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|پِٹْرولِیَم|m}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|نېفىت}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|neft}}\n* Venetan: {{tt|vec|petrojo|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|dầu mỏ}}\n* Welsh: {{tt|cy|petroliwm|n}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|נאַפֿט}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|epo rọ̀bì}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|petrol}}\n* Zulu: {{tt|zu|uwoyela}}, {{tt|zu|i-oyili}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Latin: {{t+check|la|oleum|m}}\n* Vilamovian: {{t-check|wym|ył}}\n* Woiwurrung: {{t-check|wyi|yn-nok}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|oilen}}, {{m|enm|oylen}}, from the noun (see above).\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[lubricate]] with oil.\n#: {{hyper|en|lubricate#Verb}}\n#: {{hypo|en|overoil#Verb|reoil#Verb|underoil#Verb}}\n#: {{cot|en|grease#Verb}}\n#* {{RQ:Baum Wizard of Oz|passage=Before they went to see Glinda, however, they were taken to a room of the Castle, where Dorothy washed her face and combed her hair, and the Lion shook the dust out of his mane, and the Scarecrow patted himself into his best shape, and the Woodman polished his tin and '''oiled''' his joints.|23}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1955|month=February|author=E. J. Tyler and J. Quanjer|title=The Steam Locomotive in Holland 1919-1954|journal=Railway Magazine|page=131|text=Platform faces in Holland are further back from the track than they are in Britain, and it is a common thing to see a driver standing quite comfortably between his engine and the platform while '''oiling''' the motion.}}\n#* {{RQ:Allingham China Governess|chapter=17|passage=The face which emerged was not reassuring.{{nb...}}. He was not a mongol but there was a deficiency of a sort there, and it was not made more pretty by a latter-day hair cut which involved eccentrically long elf-locks and '''oiled''' black curls.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[grease]] with oil for [[cook]]ing.\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[fuel]] with oil.\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|idiomatic}} To [[say]] in an [[unctuous]] [[manner]].\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=22 Dec 84|volume=12|number=23|journal=Gay Community News|page=10|author=Michael Bronski|title=Women Act Out on Film|text=\"Do you need a drink?\" '''oils''' Robert Ryan to the disinterested Stanwyck in ''Clash By Night''; \"Let's ''say'' that's what I need,\" she sneers back.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|reoil|self-oiling|squeaky wheels get oiled|unoil}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|lubricate with oil}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|yağlamaq}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|urindatu}}, {{t|eu|urineztatu}}, {{t|eu|koipeztatu}}, {{t|eu|labainarazi}}, {{t|eu|lubrifikatu}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|смазвам}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|naolejovat}}\n* Dalmatian: {{t|dlm|engrassur}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|smøre}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|oliën}}, {{t+|nl|smeren}}\n* Egyptian: {{t-egy|gs|h=gs:z-W22:D40}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|olei}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|öljytä}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|huiler}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|დაზეთვა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|ölen}}, {{t+|de|einölen}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|λαδώνω}} {{qualifier|a gun}}; {{t+|el|λιπαίνω}} {{qualifier|machinery}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|שימן|tr=shimén}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|olajoz}}, {{t+|hu|beolajoz}}, {{t+|hu|megolajoz}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|oliare}}, {{t|it|oleare}}\n* Japanese: [[油]]を[[塗る]] (あぶらをぬる, abura o nuru)\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|چەورکردن}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|lūbricō}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|eļļot}}, {{t|lv|ieeļļot}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|подмачкува}}, {{t|mk|намачкува}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|तेल लावणे}}\n* Mongolian: {{t+|mn|тослох}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|olje}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|oliwić|impf}}, {{t+|pl|naoliwić|pf}}, {{t+|pl|naoliwiać|impf}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|olear}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|сма́зывать}}, {{t+|ru|сма́зать}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|подмазати}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|podmazati}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|lubbrificari}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|naoljiti}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|aceitar}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|olja}}, {{t+|sv|smörja}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|నూనె దీపము}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|yağlamak}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|یاغلامق|tr=yağlamak}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|ron kerden}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to grease with oil for cooking}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|yağlamaq}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|greixar}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|invetten}}, {{t+|nl|oliën}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|olei}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|voidella}}, {{t+|fi|rasvata}}\n* German: [[mit]] [[Öl]] [[bestreichen]]\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|שימן|tr=shimén}}\n* Hungarian: {{t|hu|[[olaj]]at [[hozzátesz|tesz hozzá]]}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|oliare}}, {{t|it|oleare}}\n* Japanese: [[油]]を[[ひく]] (あぶらをひく, abura o hiku)\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|taukot}}, {{t|lv|ietaukot}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|подмачкува}}, {{t|mk|намачкува}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|तेल घालणे}}\n* Mongolian: {{t+|mn|тослох}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|olje}}, {{t+|no|smøre}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|olear}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|науљити}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|nauljiti}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|nzunziari}}, {{t|scn|nzivari}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|engrasar}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|olja}}, {{t+|sv|smörja}}\n* Turkish:\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|یاغلامق|tr=yağlamak}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|ruwen kerden}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=ilo|ILO|LOI|Loi|Oli}}\n\n{{C|en|Petroleum|Fats and oils|Liquids}}\n{{cln|en|calculator words}}\n\n==Irish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ga|/ɛlʲ/|/ɪlʲ/|ref2={{R:ga:Finck|II|89}}}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymid|ga|disgrace}}\nFrom {{inh|ga|sga|ail}}, {{m|sga|oil|t=disgrace, reproach}}.<ref>{{R:DIL|955|head=2 ail (‘disgrace, reproach’)}}</ref>\n\n====Noun====\n{{ga-noun|f|~e|-}}\n\n# {{lb|ga|literary}} [[disgrace]], [[reproach]]; act of [[reproaching]]\n# {{lb|ga|literary}} [[blemish]], [[defect]]\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{ga-decl-f2-nopl|o|il|ile}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|ga|nourish}}\n{{root|ga|ine-pro|*h₂el-|id=grow}}\nFrom {{inh|ga|sga|ailid}}, {{m|sga|oilid|t=nourishes, rears, fosters}} (compare {{m|ga|altram|t=fosterage}}, from a verbal noun of {{m|sga|ailid}}).<ref>{{R:DIL|1016|head=1 ailid (‘nourish, foster’}}</ref>\n\n====Verb====\n{{ga-verb|pres=oileann|fut=oilfidh|vn=oiliúint|pp=~te}}\n\n# {{lb|ga|transitive}} [[nourish]], [[rear]], [[foster]]\n#: Proverb: {{ux|ga|Gach dalta mar a '''oiltear'''.|inline=1|Every fosterling as it '''is reared'''.}}\n# {{lb|ga|transitive}} [[train]], [[educate]]\n#: {{ux|ga|lámh '''oilte'''|inline=1|'''practised''' hand}}\n\n=====Conjugation=====\n{{ga-conj-1a|o|i|l|slender|vn=oiliúint}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|ga|ailiúnas}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{etymid|ga|stone}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{ga-noun|f|oileach|~eacha}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|ga|ail||stone, rock}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{ga-decl-f5|o|il|ileach|ileacha}}\n\n===Etymology 4===\n{{etymid|ga|suit}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{ga-verb|pres=~eann|fut=~fidh|vn=oiliúint|pp=~te}}\n\n# {{lb|ga|intransitive}} {{alternative form of|ga|oir||suit, fit, become}}\n\n=====Conjugation=====\n{{ga-conj-1a|o|i|l|slender|vn=oiliúint}}\n\n===Mutation===\n{{ga-mut}}\n\n===References===\n{{reflist|size=smaller}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ga:Ó Dónaill}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|oyle}}\n\n==Old French==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{af|fro|o|il}}, possibly from:\n* {{inh|fro|la-vul|*hoc ille}}, from Latin {{m|la|[[hoc]] + [[ille]]||this [is what] he [said]}},<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=Cm3xl7C9Rh4C Languages Within Language], by Ivan Fonagy, [http://books.google.com/books?id=Cm3xl7C9Rh4C&pg=PA66&lpg=PA66&dq=oui+%22hoc+ille%22 page 66]</ref> akin to {{m|fro|o}} {{m|fro|je}}, {{m|fro|o}} {{m|fro|tu}}, {{m|fro|o}} {{m|fro|nos}}, {{m|fro|o}} {{m|fr|vos}}, all ‘this’ constructed with other [[personal pronoun]]s;<ref>{{R:fr:TLFi|oui}}</ref><ref>[http://stella.atilf.fr ''Trésor de la Langue Française informatisé''] at atilf.fr; select “OÏL”</ref>\n* {{m|la|[[hoc]] [[illud]]||this is it, ''lit.'' this that}}.\nIn any case, an elliptical phrase of response, by semantic erosion/{{w|grammaticalization}} possibly [[calque]]d on {{der|fro|cel-gau|-}}: compare Portuguese and Spanish {{m|pt|isso}} and {{m|es|eso|t=yes, yeah|lit=this}}, Celtic languages such as Old Irish {{m|sga|tó||yes}}, Welsh {{m|cy|do||indeed}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*só|*tod|this, that}}.<ref>Peter Schrijver, ''Studies in the History of Celtic Pronouns and Particles'', Maynooth, 1997, 15.</ref>\n\nCompare with {{cog|fro|[[o]], [[ou]], [[oc]], [[ec]], [[euc]], [[uoc]]}}, {{cog|pro|oc}} ({{cog|oc|òc}}), all from the simple {{cog|la|hoc}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{l|fro|oïl}} {{q|almost always used by scholars to disambiguate with other meanings}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|fro|/uˈil/}}\n\n====Adverb====\n{{fro-adv}}\n\n# [[yes]]\n\n====Interjection====\n{{head|fro|interjection}}\n\n# [[yes]]\n#* {{quote-text|fro|year=c. 1170|author=w:Chrétien de Troyes|title=s:fr:Érec et Énide\n|passage=\"'''Oïl''', mout m'an sovient il bien.<br>Seneschaus, savez vos an rien?\n|translation=Yes, I remember it well<br>[[seneschal|Seneschal]], do you know anything about it?}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desctree|fr|oui}}\n* {{desc|nrf|oui}} {{qualifier|Guernsey}}\n\n====References====\n<references/>\n\n===Etymology 2===\nSee {{m|fro|ueil}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|fro|/ˈɔ(i̯)ʎ/}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{fro-noun|m}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|fro|ueil}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|fro\n|year=1260–1267\n|author=w:Brunetto Latini\n|title=Livres dou Tresor\n|trans-title={{w|Book of Treasures}}\n|year2=1863\n|compiler2=Polycarpe Chabaille\n|title2=Li livres dou tresor par Brunetto Latini\n|url2=https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k29286n/f3.item\n|location2=Paris\n|publisher2=Imprimerie impériale\n|page2=203\n|pageurl2=https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k29286n/f243.item\n|chapter=De tous Faucons\n|chapter_number=150\n|chapter_series=Book 5\n|trans-chapter=On all falcons\n|chapterurl=https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k29286n/f242.item\n|text=La sisisme ligne est sourpoins. Cist est molt grans, et resemble aigle blanche, mais des '''oilz''' et des eles et dou bec est il semblables au girfaut\n|t=The sixth kind [of falcon] is the saker. It is very large, and resembles the white eagle; but in the '''eyes''', and in the wings, and in the beak, it is similar to the gyrfalcon\n}}\n\n{{C|fro|Anatomy}}\n\n==Simeulue==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|smr|noun}}\n\n# [[water]]\n# [[sap]]\n\n===References===\n* Blust's Austronesian Comparative Dictionary"}}